The White House supports United Nations Secretary General Ban Ki-moon's candidacy for a second term. They acknowledge the critical role the UN has played under Ban's leadership, including responding to crises in Cote d'Ivoire, Haiti, South Sudan, and Libya. While recognizing the UN's imperfections, the US supports reform efforts to improve effectiveness, streamline bureaucracy, reduce costs, and update business practices. They emphasize the UN's mandate to promote global peace and security, human rights, and development.